Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Main,,0,0,0,,A
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.14,0:00:06.81,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Leone Abbacchio became a police officer \N after graduating from high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.81,0:00:10.53,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,His motivation for joining the force \N stemmed purely from his innate sense of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.11,0:00:14.16,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,But not long after becoming a police officer \N as he had always dreamed... {The line needs to be shrunk a bit... find a way to shorten "as he had always dreamed", perhaps? -JMFW}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.16,0:00:18.33,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...Abbacchio became aware of \N the incongruous nature of the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.33,0:00:21.96,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,While the police willingly \N risked their lives to protect others...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.96,0:00:26.13,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...these very people who \N they were sworn to serve...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.13,0:00:32.09,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...deceived them, committed theft, \N injured others in hit-and-runs...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.51,0:00:32.09,Flashback,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,{\an8}Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.09,0:00:34.80,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...and threw stones \N through police car windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.68,0:00:38.35,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,Ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.35,0:00:39.51,Flashback,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.31,0:00:41.56,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.56,0:00:43.18,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,You're a cop, aren't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.18,0:00:51.15,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,The masses were ungrateful, demanding, insulting, \N and disparaged the police, questioning their competency.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.15,0:00:55.86,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Even when the police risked their lives \N to arrest the lowest of the low... {Netflix Eva PTSD intensifies. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.86,0:01:02.12,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...the law was lenient towards those with money,\N resulting in many being set free. {Hijacking this line to comment on the TS: I don't suppose this is reasonably de-hardsubbable? If not, suggesting to reduce the font size for the English TS. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.12,0:01:03.96,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,Quit causing us so much trouble! {Maybe more like: Keeping after you is a pain in the ass, man! -JMFW}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.96,0:01:04.75,Flashback,Isacco,0,0,0,,Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.75,0:01:06.08,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,Well, what's done is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.42,0:01:08.84,Flashback,Guy,0,0,0,,{\an8}We just gotta find us some suckers to scam.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.42,0:01:10.30,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Eventually, Abbacchio began to \N take this incongruity to heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.46,0:01:17.51,Flashback,Pimp,0,0,0,,Come on, Officer... \N Cut us a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.51,0:01:22.68,Flashback,Pimp,0,0,0,,This young lady's dad is up to his neck in debt, \N and she needs the dough.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.68,0:01:24.77,Flashback,Pimp,0,0,0,,We ain't bothering no one!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.77,0:01:26.64,Flashback,Girl,0,0,0,,Hey, what's the hold up?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.64,0:01:28.10,Flashback,Girl,0,0,0,,I have another client waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.10,0:01:29.56,Flashback,Pimp,0,0,0,,Christ, I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.57,0:01:37.61,Flashback,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Even if I arrested them, \N they'd just post bail and be released.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.61,0:01:42.87,Flashback,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,The only difference is whether they pay \N the court and their lawyers, or me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.08,0:01:47.37,Flashback,Pimp,0,0,0,,You're a swell guy, mister...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.37,0:01:50.67,Flashback,Pimp,0,0,0,,Real swell for a cop...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.01,0:01:59.76,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,One night, a report was received\N about an armed robbery at a shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.84,0:01:59.76,Flashback,Cop Buddy,0,0,0,,{\an8}Abbacchio! You take the back! {This is his name now. Remember it for episode 28 or suffer his fate!!!! -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.52,0:02:08.02,Flashback,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Freeze! You're under arrest!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.86,0:02:14.03,Flashback,Pimp,0,0,0,,H-Hey, you again...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.69,0:02:17.65,Flashback,Pimp,0,0,0,,I really fucked up this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.49,0:02:16.78,Flashback,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,{\an8}You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.11,0:02:21.37,Flashback,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,He was shot in the head...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.37,0:02:24.33,Flashback,Pimp,0,0,0,,Hey, can't you just tell 'em \N you didn't see nothin'?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.33,0:02:26.20,Flashback,Pimp,0,0,0,,Come on, lemme go!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.20,0:02:28.50,Flashback,Pimp,0,0,0,,I swear I'll be good!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.50,0:02:29.96,Flashback,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,No! You're under arrest!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.96,0:02:32.88,Flashback,Pimp,0,0,0,,Come on, think about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.88,0:02:38.13,Flashback,Pimp,0,0,0,,If you arrest me, \N word'll spread that you took a bribe!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.72,0:02:42.14,Flashback,Pimp,0,0,0,,That gun's real scary...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.14,0:02:44.72,Flashback,Pimp,0,0,0,,Could ya not point it at me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.69,0:02:51.19,Flashback,Cop Buddy,0,0,0,,Abbacchio! \N He's got a gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.90,0:03:01.11,Flashback,Pimp,0,0,0,,Oww! That hurt! Fucking shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.11,0:03:03.45,Flashback,Pimp,0,0,0,,I'm dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.45,0:03:04.66,Flashback,Pimp,0,0,0,,I'm dead...!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.20,0:03:06.45,Flashback,Pimp,0,0,0,,I'm dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.45,0:03:08.41,Flashback,Pimp,0,0,0,,I'm so dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.38,0:03:21.63,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,At that moment, \N Abbacchio's future ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.72,0:03:31.94,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,In addition to the corruption charges, \N his actions had inadvertently led to the death of his partner...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.94,0:03:35.31,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...and for that, he would bear a cross \N he could never put down again. {The literal here is "He was shouldered with a cross he could never put down". I dunno I kinda feel like that phrasing is a bit more poetic? -Starfish}{Seconded. - Toa}{Thirded. -Axel}{Fourthded. The original line was "...and for that, he would have to \N bear the guilt for the rest of his life." -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.31,0:03:40.61,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,It was at this point that his \N body and soul were consumed by darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.61,0:03:45.12,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,Whether anyone else died, \N or he lost all his limbs...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.12,0:03:47.58,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,...his heart would forever \N remain unswayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.59,0:04:06.93,Flashback,Bruno,0,0,0,,Abbacchio, isn't it?
